At least £300billion of UK pension money is invested in companies linked to destroying trees, his Make My Money Matter campaign has found.  The Blackadder creator, 65, wants people to switch funds to businesses restoring the environment. He said: "Now is the moment to take heroic action to protect our planet."  In Britain, £2 in every £10 invested in an average pension is linked to forest loss. At least 30 football pitchesworth of trees are axed every minute globally, figures show. 